2) Food Delivery System using Spring Factory Pattern
=========================================================

Problem Statement:
You are developing a Food Delivery System where users can order food from different restaurants.
The system supports:
Pizza
Burger
Biryani

Each food type has its own preparation message, but all follow a common interface.
Use Spring Core + Factory Design Pattern (Map Injection only) to dynamically create the required food object based on user input.

Requirements:
==================

1️) Create interface Food
String prepareFood();

2️) Create implementation classes:
Pizza
Burger
Biryani
Conditions:
Annotate with @Component
Use names:
"pizza"
"burger"
"biryani"
Output:
Pizza → "Preparing Pizza..."
Burger → "Preparing Burger..."
Biryani → "Preparing Biryani..."

3️) Create Factory class FoodFactory
Annotate with @Component
Use:
@Autowired
private Map<String, Food> foodMap;
Method:
public Food getFood(String type)
Logic:
Return object using map
If invalid → throw exception

4️) Create Config class
@Configuration
@ComponentScan

5️) Main class
Take input (food type)
Call factory
Print result

Sample Output:
--------------
Enter food type: biryani
Preparing Biryani...

